devdoc.details: You can set the FiubaCoin contract to buy packages and the Sticker contract to generate the stickers when you open a package

buyPackages(uint256).details: Tries to transfer from FiubaCoin address the necesary FiubaCoins to get the required packages

params._quantity: The quantity of required packages to buy

getAmountOfPackagesFrom(address).details: Access to a mapping to get the number of packages associated to an address

returns._0: amount Quantity of packages associated to a specify wallet

openPackage().details: If the user have packages, you can get Stickers from this function

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._coinAddress: The FiubaCoin address to be setted

setPrice(uint256).details: Only the owner of this contract could change the price

setStickerAddress(address).details: Only the owner of this contract could set this address

params._stickerAddress: The Sticker address to be setted

setStickersPerPackage(uint256).details: This funtion sets the quantity of sticker per package and verify if the inserted amount as parameter is bigger than zero

params._amount: A new amount of stickers per package

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
